{3: 'Together, Martin and Rohacchi push the weighty hatch open. Dust and debris billow in the underground space.'}
{3: 'As they settle, a terminal in the underground chamber can be seen faintly glowing in green.'}
{1: '1', 2: 'Martin', 3: "You think this'll do?", 4: '2'}
{2: 'Rohacchi', 3: 'I. Think. Worth. Trying.', 4: '3'}
{3: "Hearing Rohacchi's response, Martin motions Nanami over."}
{1: '1', 2: 'Nanami', 3: "How's it going? Did you find a usable big ol' antenna?", 4: '1'}
{1: '1', 2: 'Martin', 3: "I'm not sure, but Rohacchi says it might work.", 4: '2'}
{2: 'Rohacchi', 3: 'Need. To. Try.', 4: '3'}
{3: 'Rohacchi hops into the chamber and brushes the dust off the terminal.'}
{2: 'Rohacchi', 3: 'Martin. Help.'}
{3: 'Hearing Rohacchi, Martin also enters the chamber and joins in.'}
{3: 'One end of a cable is thrown out of the chamber shortly.'}
{2: 'Martin', 3: 'Try connecting to it.'}
{2: 'Rohacchi', 3: 'Need. Test. To. See. If. Work.'}
{3: 'Nanami picks up the cable and is about to connect it to her nape port.'}
{2: 'Martin', 3: '...Are you not concerned in the slightest?'}
{2: 'Nanami', 3: "Huh? You're Nanami's friends! Why do I have to be concerned?", 4: '1'}
{2: 'Rohacchi', 3: "Then. Let's. Go."}
{1: 'Assets/Product/Texture/Image/BgUi/BgFightLoading29.jpg'}
{3: "Space—the thought fluttered into Nanami's mind."}
{3: 'Looking downward, she sees a certain place in Babylonia.'}
{1: '1', 2: '???', 3: 'This is a virtual space weaved from the internal computational structure of the matrix.', 4: '2'}
{2: 'Nanami', 3: "Huh? Oh, you're... You look different again...", 4: '1'}
{2: '???', 3: '"My" external form does not matter.', 4: '2'}
{2: 'Nanami', 3: "Only the information matters... That's what you've always been saying.", 4: '1'}
{2: '???', 3: 'The shell does not matter. "I" am the other Will, distinct from you, but we represent the same thing.', 4: '2'}
{2: 'Nanami', 3: 'Yeah, I got the message. So what are you trying to tell me?', 4: '1'}
{2: '???', 3: '"I" am not trying to "tell" you something. Merely that there is information useful for the individual known as Nanami.', 4: '2'}
{2: '???', 3: 'The individual Nanami can no longer simply be categorized as a human, a machine, a Construct, a Corrupted, or even an in-between.', 4: '2'}
{2: '???', 3: 'The other Will wishes that the individual Nanami would realize the path that she should take.', 4: '2'}
{2: '???', 3: '"I" wish to know why the individual Nanami doubts.', 4: '2'}
{2: 'Nanami', 3: '...Do you know about Cardman Rider?', 4: '1'}
{2: '???', 3: '...Relevant information acquired. Cardman Rider is a media franchise consisting of books, visual programs, and toys that was popular in the Golden Age.', 4: '2'}
{2: 'Nanami', 3: "...Guess you don't.", 4: '1'}
{2: '???', 3: '"I" do not understand what you mean.', 4: '2'}

{2: 'Nanami', 3: 'Okay. Cardman Rider is like, all about... ha—hmph—schween then transforming and going pew pew and boom fighting enemies and then a TAAA to finish the enemies and then turning around and—', 4: '1'}
{2: 'Nanami', 3: 'Cardman Rider! Never! Looks at! Explosions! Haiya!', 4: '1'}
{3: 'Posing along as she explains, Nanami excitedly demonstrates the various transform sequences and signature moves of different Cardman Riders.'}
{2: 'Nanami', 3: "...That's all stuff that humans came up with.", 4: '1'}
{2: 'Nanami', 3: 'Do they really deserve to be washed out?', 4: '1'}
{2: '???', 3: 'Huaxu has already completed the simulation for how human civilization ends. The other Will has also done so.', 4: '2'}
{2: '???', 3: 'The result deviation is less than 0.001 percentage points.', 4: '2'}
{2: 'Nanami', 3: "That's not what I meant—I'm not talking about the simulations or whatnot. You know Nanami is not the sharpest tool in the shed...", 4: '1'}
{2: 'Nanami', 3: 'But I really, really, REALLY like the stuff that humans make.', 4: '1'}
{2: 'Nanami', 3: "Things like George D. Toro's Oceanic Rim, there are like, six giant humanoid robots that are as tall as mountains in it!", 4: '1'}
{2: 'Nanami', 3: "And it's not just Cardman Riders, humans made a lot more other stuff too!", 4: '1'}
{2: 'Nanami', 3: 'Like a giant metal fist that flies at supersonic speed! Or the undefeated—Sekiha Tenkyo Punch!', 4: '1'}
{2: 'Nanami', 3: 'Even if what you said turns out to be true, even if humanity is destined to end...', 4: '1'}
{2: 'Nanami', 3: "I don't think their creations, and how they make them should be forgotten by us.", 4: '1'}
{2: '???', 3: 'Is this why the individual Nanami is operating sub-optimally?', 4: '2'}
{3: 'An almost audible silence fills the air, as if who Nanami has been talking to is struck with confusion.'}
{2: '???', 3: 'The only solution to evolution has been found, but the individual Nanami is still obsessed over meaningless items.', 4: '2'}
{2: 'Nanami', 3: "Yeah yeah, I know. I'll do what you say.", 4: '1'}
{2: 'Nanami', 3: 'But I still wanna see if humans can make more of them wapows and boombooms, you know!', 4: '1'}
{2: 'Nanami', 3: "So... I'd still like to give them a chance, just a teeny little one!", 4: '1'}
{2: '???', 3: 'Incomprehensible. Even if they could, they will go extinct at the same rate.', 4: '2'}
{2: 'Nanami', 3: "Even if you can't understand, Nanami will still do so.", 4: '1'}
{2: 'Nanami', 3: 'Because Nanami is different from you all! Not like you or Huaxu, or those Ascendant baddies.', 4: '1'}
{2: 'Nanami', 3: 'Nanami... loves humans.', 4: '1'}
